subdefinitions.definition: Ability , skilfulness , especially skill in making plans and carrying them into execution ; dexterity in managing affairs, adroitness , practical cunning ; ingenuity in constructing , dexterity [9th century] .
Cunning , art, skill, or dexterity applied to bad purposes; artifice ; guile ; subtlety ; shrewdness as demonstrated by being skilled in deception [13th century] .

definitions.definition: A work or product of art [c. 1000] .

subdefinitions.definition: Handmade items , especially domestic or decorative objects ; handicrafts [20th century] .

definitions.label_groups: countable , obsolete in the general sense

definitions.definition: A device , a means ; a magical device, spell or enchantment [13th century] .
Learning of the schools, scholarship ; a branch of learning or knowledge , a science , especially one of the ‘seven liberal arts ’ of the medieval universities [13th century] .
Skill, skilfulness, art, especially the skill needed for a particular profession [9th century] .

A branch of skilled work or trade , especially one requiring manual dexterity or artistic skill, but sometimes applied equally to any business , calling or profession ; the skilled practice of a practical occupation [since the 9th century] .
examples: He learned his craft as an apprentice.

definitions.definition: A trade or profession as embodied in its practitioners collectively; the members of a trade or handicraft as a body; an association of these; a trade's union , guild , or ‘ company ’ [15th century] .
examples: She represented the craft of brewers .

definitions.definition: A vehicle designed for navigation in or on water or air or through outer space [since the 17th century] .

subdefinitions.definition: Boats , especially of smaller size than ships . Historically primarily applied to vessels engaged in loading or unloading of other vessels, as lighters , hoys , and barges .
Those vessels attendant on a fleet , such as cutters , schooners , and gunboats , generally commanded by lieutenants .

definitions.definition: Implements used in catching fish , such as net , line , or hook . Modern use primarily in whaling , as in harpoons , hand-lances , etc. [17th century] .

main_definition: ( uncountable , obsolete ) Strength ; power ; might ; force [9th century] .
